SIMPLE: profit
RECORDS: 3

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Profit
<hw>Pro"fit</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F., fr. L.
<ets>profectus</ets> advance, progress, profit, fr.
<ets>profectum</ets>. See <er>Proficient</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Acquisition beyond expenditure; excess of value received for
producing, keeping, or selling, over cost; hence, pecuniary gain in any
transaction or occupation; emolument; <as>as, a <ex>profit</ex> on the
sale of goods</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Let no man anticipate uncertain <qex>profits</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Rambler.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Accession of good; valuable results; useful
consequences; benefit; avail; gain; as, an office of
<xex>profit</xex>,</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>This I speak for your own <qex>profit</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>1 Cor.
vii. 35.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>If you dare do yourself a <qex>profit</qex> and a right.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Benefit; avail; service; improvement;
advancement; gain; emolument.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Profit</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Profit
<hw>Prof"it</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos>
<conjf>Profited</conjf>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Profiting</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[F. <ets>profiter</ets>. See
<er>Profit</er>, <pos>n.</pos>]</ety> <def>To be of service to; to be
good to; to help on; to benefit; to advantage; to avail; to aid; <as>as,
truth <ex>profits</ex> all men</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The word preached did not <qex>profit them</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Heb. iv. 2.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>It is a great means of <qex>profiting</qex> yourself, to copy
diligently excellent pieces and beautiful designs.</q>
<rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Profit</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Profit
<hw>Prof"it</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To gain advantage;
to make improvement; to improve; to gain; to advance.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I <qex>profit</qex> not by thy talk.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To be of use or advantage; to do or bring
good.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Riches <qex>profit</qex> not in the day of wrath.</q>
<rj><qau>Prov. xi. 4.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Profitable</ent>⟦br⟧
